<section class="Bio">
    <h2>Biography</h2>
    <p>Steven Paul Jobs (February 24, 1955 â€“ October 5, 2011) was an American businessman, inventor, and investor best known for co-founding Apple Inc. in 1976, 
        which later became the world's largest technology company by revenue and the largest company in the world by market capitalization.
         Jobs was also the founder of NeXT and chairman and majority shareholder of Pixar. 
        He was a pioneer of the personal computer revolution of the 1970s and 1980s, along with his early business partner and fellow Apple co-founder Steve Wozniak.</p>
